    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1 Alanyl Spider Oligopeptide-1 Hexapeptide-40) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sr-Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1, sr-Spider Oligopeptide-1, and Hexapeptide-40 with the initiation code for alanine. The fusion peptide contains 497 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
